-- California Inmate-Release Order to Get Top Court Review Amid State Deficit
-- Greg Stohr
-- 2010-06-14T14:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/california-inmate-release-order-to-get-top-court-review-amid-state-deficit.html

          
          
             The  U.S. Supreme Court  agreed to
review an order that would require California to reduce its
prison population by 46,000 within two years to ease
overcrowding.  
 Governor  Arnold Schwarzenegger  and a group of Republican
state lawmakers contend that the lower court order conflicts
with a federal law aimed at reducing prison litigation. The
three-judge panel said the reduction is needed to remedy the
constitutionally inadequate level of medical and mental health
care inmates are receiving.  
 Under a plan submitted by the state in January, California
would use county jails and home detention to alleviate the
overcrowding. California, the nationâ€™s most populous state, is
facing a $19 billion budget deficit.  
 The case is Schwarzenegger v. Plata, 09-1233.  
